<Base title="About - Matt Wright">
  <a href="/" class="back-link">← Matt Wright's website</a>

  <h1>Matt Wright</h1>

  <div class="markdown-body">
    <p>
      Matt Wright is CEO and Co-founder of <a href="https://evmsystems.ai" target="_blank">EVM Systems</a>, building agentic infrastructure and products for the agent economy. The thesis: self-owned AI requires three layers — open models and inference (<a href="https://gaianet.ai" target="_blank">Gaia</a>), agentic infrastructure (<a href="https://xo.ai" target="_blank">XO</a>), and local compute (<a href="https://one.olares.com/" target="_blank">Olares</a>). EVM Systems sits at the center of this stack, shipping products for startups, enterprise, and Web3.
    </p>

    <p>
      Matt co-founded <a href="https://gaianet.ai" target="_blank">Gaia</a>, a decentralized open-source AI infrastructure network that grew to 710,000+ nodes, 30+ trillion inferences, and 110+ strategic integrations with partners including Coinbase, EigenLayer, ENS, MetaMask/Consensys, and Moonpay. He led the project from concept through a $20M raise, token launch, the Gaia AI Phone on Samsung Galaxy S25, and the formation of the Gaia Foundation and DAO.
    </p>

    <p>
      At <a href="https://consensys.io" target="_blank">ConsenSys</a>, Matt held multiple leadership roles — Director of Developer Relations, Director of Decentralized Community &amp; DAOs, and Director of the Fellowship Program. He shaped developer GTM and token economics strategies for 400k+ developers across products like MetaMask and Infura, and led ConsenSys' approach to DAO tooling and decentralized governance.
    </p>

    <p>
      At <a href="https://www.jpmorgan.com" target="_blank">J.P. Morgan</a>, Matt bootstrapped a developer community around Quorum, the open-source enterprise Ethereum platform. He built a 50+ member global Ambassador program across 25+ countries, scaled the ecosystem 5x, and drove the visibility and enterprise credibility that laid the groundwork for Quorum's acquisition by ConsenSys.
    </p>

    <p>
      Matt's career in developer communities started at <a href="https://angelhack.com" target="_blank">AngelHack</a>, where as Director of Community Development he grew the global developer base from 50k to 200k members across 75+ countries, powered by 200+ Ambassadors. His team organized 150+ hackathons for Fortune 500 companies including Mastercard, Motorola, ABInBev, RBC, Barclays, U.S. Chamber of Commerce, and UBS — partnering with local tech communities, NGOs, universities, accelerators, and government agencies across North America, Latin America, Asia-Pacific, and Mainland China.
    </p>

    <p>
      Outside of these roles, Matt co-founded <a href="https://daonyc.xyz" target="_blank">DAO NYC</a> and <a href="https://wgmi.io" target="_blank">Wgmi</a>, and has organized some of the most memorable events in crypto — including the Korea Blockchain Week Official Afterparty with <a href="https://www.chrislakemusic.com/" target="_blank">Chris Lake</a>, Metahills in Beverly Hills with <a href="https://tokimonsta.com/" target="_blank">TOKiMONSTA</a> and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/ayybomusic/" target="_blank">Ayybo</a>, Gn at NFT NYC with <a href="https://claudevonstroke.com/" target="_blank">Claude VonStroke</a> (<a href="https://time.com/6115274/nft-conference-parties-culture/" target="_blank">featured in TIME</a>), and the Gaia Launch Party at Token2049 with <a href="https://www.diplo.com/" target="_blank">Diplo</a>. He is a member of MetaCartel DAO and has contributed to 25+ DAOs.
    </p>

    <p>
      Matt's work has been featured in <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/amyguttman/2025/09/01/the-founder-betting-on-a-decentralized-future-for-ai/" target="_blank">Forbes</a>, <a href="https://cointelegraph.com/news/web3-gaia-hardware-crypto-phones-consoles" target="_blank">Cointelegraph</a>, <a href="https://decrypt.co/297060/gaia-is-building-living-knowledge-systems-for-ai-agents" target="_blank">Decrypt</a>, <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/gaianet-secures-10m-build-decentralized-183000076.html" target="_blank">Yahoo Finance</a>, <a href="https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/gaia-partners-with-eigenlayer-to-bring-powerful-avs-security-to-decentralized-ai-1033946119" target="_blank">Business Insider</a>, <a href="https://www.theblock.co/post/252044/consensys-web3-fellowship-program-fund" target="_blank">The Block</a>, and <a href="https://time.com/6115274/nft-conference-parties-culture/" target="_blank">TIME</a>. He has spoken at <a href="https://consensus2025.coindesk.com/agenda/speaker/-matt-wright" target="_blank">Consensus</a>, Token2049, ETHDenver, Korea Blockchain Week, and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SWaU8b4tthw" target="_blank">MIT</a>.
    </p>

